answerCode:
// Problem: Without keys, Flutter's reconciler matches widgets
// by their position in the tree. When an item is removed from
// the middle, all widgets below it shift up and Flutter may
// assign stale state (e.g., text field content, animations)
// to the wrong items.

// Fix: Use a ValueKey with a unique, stable identifier
Column(
  children: items.map((item) =>
    MyItemWidget(
      key: ValueKey(item.id), // Stable identity
      label: item.label,
    )
  ).toList(),
)

// With keys, Flutter correctly matches existing widgets to
// their previous state even after reordering or removal.
// Use ValueKey for data-driven keys, ObjectKey for object identity.

